      },
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.14 GPa) was adopted for Ti-6Al-4V based on ASTM-certified coupon testing from two material lots. Frictional contact (Coulomb, mu=0.2) was selected based on published tribological data for Ti-Ti interfaces under lubricated conditions. The model form is consistent with FDA guidance on metallic spinal implant FEA and with the three-laboratory ensemble approach used in the Nagaraja study."
