        "description": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) must be demonstrably equivalent to the as-tested experimental configuration; equivalency documented by traceable measurement records."
      },
      "rationale": "Equivalency between the FEA model and the physical test specimens was established through CMM geometry capture, certified material lot data, and direct replication of ASTM F1717 fixture geometry in the boundary conditions. A formal equivalency matrix was compiled mapping each FEA input parameter to its experimental counterpart with measurement uncertainty. No unresolved discrepancies were identified."
